{
  "stem": "4284.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you were not likely to cut it off and sew it on, and cut it off and sew it on again.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So it could not be pinned on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's how we got the star, and of course from then on you were obviously totally I guess you might say a sore in even a walking population because you just stood out with an insignia on back and on your chest.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course that intimidated everybody not to go anywhere unless you absolutely had to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think anybody can understand-- unless you are perhaps racially different and can be recognized as being like none of the majority-- what it's like to have to be so labeled and so marked.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then have supposedly tried to live not a normal life, but just a, a meager existence.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In 1939 and thereafter, things deteriorated even worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Without going into gruesome details for that--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the personal experience was that I did make an attempt once to use a street car because I had to-- I wanted to, and I don't even remember what my mission was to even take the chance.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I stood on the street car, on the steps and holding on to a rail.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's very similar as we have transportation in San Francisco in the cable car.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You didn't take a chance to go in there, and certainly never, ever would you have the nerve or courage to sit down and take a place when a Gentile would have to stand up.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was just impossible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I hung on for probably something like seven or eight blocks.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, it was, of course, wonderful sport for somebody on the street car to kick and try to push me off while I was riding the streetcar.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
